    <item>
      <title>I’ve been taking a quieter season after a very full year of teaching, retreats, ...</title>
      <link>https://www.instagram.com/p/DVGTD2aATiL/</link>
      <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/641184502_18192847993351251_3733317974650974046_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_s480x480_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=105&amp;ig_cache_key=MzgzODgzODk2MTkzNDAxMDc4Nw%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjcyMHg5NjAuc2RyLkMzIn0%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=MowsLJBpdY4Q7kNvwEiIf8L&amp;_nc_oc=AdqLPyPKX8WODX3QjvGfnru9y7OwmTeWh_r2z7W3b9C9uvWVinRASRiqqfAyhyj1c6Q&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=l83bst0JUsPmku8MBjNz3g&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_Afza87iuqrwRNITSd9dcu40Eh-_njfqniwGTN_p2H9iJMQ&amp;oe=69C9AFF0" alt="Instagram billede fra @yogabybella" /></p><p><strong>@yogabybella</strong></p><p>I’ve been taking a quieter season after a very full year of teaching, retreats, and corporate work.<br/>
<br/>
There’s a kind of momentum that can build when things are going well - more opportunities, more ideas, more output. And yet I found myself wanting to slow down, not speed up.<br/>
<br/>
Yoga, after all, is more interested in depth than momentum. We know the practice extends beyond the mat and into how we shape our lives.<br/>
<br/>
It feels grounding to be back in my hometown for a while - slowing down and letting everything gently land within the familiarity of Australia.<br/>
<br/>
There’s more to share for 2026, but it will come slowly.<br/>
<br/>
For now, here’s some of the nature that’s been nourishing me.</p>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/641184502_18192847993351251_3733317974650974046_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_s480x480_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=105&amp;ig_cache_key=MzgzODgzODk2MTkzNDAxMDc4Nw%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjcyMHg5NjAuc2RyLkMzIn0%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=MowsLJBpdY4Q7kNvwEiIf8L&amp;_nc_oc=AdqLPyPKX8WODX3QjvGfnru9y7OwmTeWh_r2z7W3b9C9uvWVinRASRiqqfAyhyj1c6Q&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=l83bst0JUsPmku8MBjNz3g&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_Afza87iuqrwRNITSd9dcu40Eh-_njfqniwGTN_p2H9iJMQ&amp;oe=69C9AFF0" alt="Instagram billede fra @yogabybella" /></p><p><strong>@yogabybella</strong></p><p>I’ve been taking a quieter season after a very full year of teaching, retreats, and corporate work.<br/>
<br/>
There’s a kind of momentum that can build when things are going well - more opportunities, more ideas, more output. And yet I found myself wanting to slow down, not speed up.<br/>
<br/>
Yoga, after all, is more interested in depth than momentum. We know the practice extends beyond the mat and into how we shape our lives.<br/>
<br/>
It feels grounding to be back in my hometown for a while - slowing down and letting everything gently land within the familiarity of Australia.<br/>
<br/>
There’s more to share for 2026, but it will come slowly.<br/>
<br/>
For now, here’s some of the nature that’s been nourishing me.</p>]]></content:encoded>
