    <item>
      <title>The real truth 😅 ‘You’re so grounded! You must be so calm when you meditate!’ …....</title>
      <link>https://www.instagram.com/p/DLAwsJxsFgC/</link>
      <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.71878-15/508649134_639825452445152_5143160928573248592_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_p360x360_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=107&amp;ig_cache_key=MzY1NzEzNzAzNzgxMTY2ODk5NA%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjY0MHgxMTM2LnNkci5DMyJ9&amp;_nc_ohc=wgjfNvsR83UQ7kNvwEfTXHa&amp;_nc_oc=Ado9MCccgibtx7ZjV1KlmDkyfXLU3qC5b7ByEpjCBZxtu0l0U2x3KPnGzoBcDqFJVt8&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=l83bst0JUsPmku8MBjNz3g&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfxADYaIiP1mZX2pJnTloQ0mR7vD0OuVSdd75XPG15I8lQ&amp;oe=69C99CF4" alt="Instagram billede fra @yogabybella" /></p><p><strong>@yogabybella</strong></p><p>The real truth 😅<br/>
<br/>
‘You’re so grounded! You must be so calm when you meditate!’ ….. meanwhile 🙃🌪️<br/>
<br/>
One of the biggest misconceptions about meditation is that we have to be totally ☁️ calm and quiet ☁️ in our minds when we do it. The point is not to get rid of thoughts but to learn how to notice them without judgement, while lengthening the spaces of time in-between those thoughts where you are simply breathing and being, rather than thinking or doing. It’s a continual practice - something to experience rather than to perfect. And I find it helps to laugh at yourself sometimes too 🌀<br/>
<br/>
If you want a meditation buddy, reach out - I have free recordings online and monthly community classes ✨🌱 or just know I’m out there practicing alongside you. Yeehaw 🤠</p>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.71878-15/508649134_639825452445152_5143160928573248592_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_p360x360_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=107&amp;ig_cache_key=MzY1NzEzNzAzNzgxMTY2ODk5NA%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjY0MHgxMTM2LnNkci5DMyJ9&amp;_nc_ohc=wgjfNvsR83UQ7kNvwEfTXHa&amp;_nc_oc=Ado9MCccgibtx7ZjV1KlmDkyfXLU3qC5b7ByEpjCBZxtu0l0U2x3KPnGzoBcDqFJVt8&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=l83bst0JUsPmku8MBjNz3g&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfxADYaIiP1mZX2pJnTloQ0mR7vD0OuVSdd75XPG15I8lQ&amp;oe=69C99CF4" alt="Instagram billede fra @yogabybella" /></p><p><strong>@yogabybella</strong></p><p>The real truth 😅<br/>
<br/>
‘You’re so grounded! You must be so calm when you meditate!’ ….. meanwhile 🙃🌪️<br/>
<br/>
One of the biggest misconceptions about meditation is that we have to be totally ☁️ calm and quiet ☁️ in our minds when we do it. The point is not to get rid of thoughts but to learn how to notice them without judgement, while lengthening the spaces of time in-between those thoughts where you are simply breathing and being, rather than thinking or doing. It’s a continual practice - something to experience rather than to perfect. And I find it helps to laugh at yourself sometimes too 🌀<br/>
<br/>
If you want a meditation buddy, reach out - I have free recordings online and monthly community classes ✨🌱 or just know I’m out there practicing alongside you. Yeehaw 🤠</p>]]></content:encoded>
